{"title_page": "Rose Gordon", "text_new": "{{Infobox person\n| name               = Rose Gordon\n| birth_name         = \n| birth_date         = \n| birth_place        = \n| death_date         = \n| death_place        = \n| occupation         = Screenwriter\n| spouse             = [[Harry S. Webb]] (div.)\n| children           = 2\n| relatives          = \n}}\n\n'''Rose Gordon''' was an American screenwriter who wrote a number of B movies in the 1930s. She served as vice president of [[Reliable Pictures]], which was owned by her husband, [[Harry S. Webb]]. She was sometimes credited as '''Harry Gordon''' or '''Homer King Gordon'''.<ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=F8OSCgAAQBAJ&pg=PA313&lpg=PA313&dq=%22rose+gordon%22+reliable+pictures&source=bl&ots=4xe9NZUAps&sig=ACfU3U19lOEcAISWiNvRMT4fVPXnJA1-9w&hl=en&sa=X&ved=2ahUKEwj6r4KFpbbjAhWGWM0KHTLZBt0Q6AEwDnoECAkQAQ#v=onepage&q=%22rose%20gordon%22%20reliable%20pictures&f=false|title=Poverty Row Studios, 1929-1940: An Illustrated History of 55 Independent Film Companies, with a Filmography for Each|last=Pitts|first=Michael R.|date=2015-09-17|publisher=McFarland|isbn=9781476610368|language=en}}</ref><ref>{{Cite book|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=VYtZAAAAMAAJ&q=%22rose+gordon%22+webb+film&dq=%22rose+gordon%22+webb+film&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiP3PjyqLbjAhVxds0KHSgBAjMQ6AEIRDAG|title=Sound films, 1927-1939: a United States filmography|last=Fetrow|first=Alan G.|date=1992-08-01|publisher=McFarland|isbn=9780899505466|language=en}}</ref>\n\n== Selected filmography ==\n\n* ''[[Wild Horse Valley (film)|Wild Horse Valley]]'' (1940) \n* ''[[El Diablo Rides]]'' (1939)\n* ''[[Santa Fe Bound]]'' (1936)\n* ''[[The Speed Reporter]]'' (1936)\n* ''[[Fast Bullets]]'' (1936)\n* ''[[Texas Jack (film)|Texas Jack]]'' (1935)\n* ''[[The Judgement Book]]'' (1935)\n* ''[[The Silver Bullet (1935 film)|The Silver Bullet]]'' (1935)\n* ''[[Silent Valley (1935 film)|Silent Valley]]'' (1935)\n* ''[[Kentucky Blue Streak]]'' (1935)\